args: Please, you must return me to my village!
You no longer have a place there.
Henceforth, you will exist in this dark\nworld and dance only for me.
(I hoped to never have that dream again.)
But now, the very thought of sleep\nterrifies me...
Looks like everything's in order here.\n...Hmm? Is that Felicia?

O moon, grant the light of peace
to all who sleep in this castle.
O stars, shine the light of hope
upon this darkened sky.
I offer my dance and prayers\nto the vast heavens above.
Good evening, Felicia.\nThat was a beautiful dance.
Ack! How long have you been there,\n{player_name}?!
Not long. I was just on my way back\nto my room when I saw you.
It's quite late to be returning to your room.\nWere you on patrol?
Something like that. Er, but maybe you\ncould keep this a secret from the others?
They're just going to tell me I should\nget more sleep if they hear about it.
Hah hah, I can imagine.\nIt will be our little secret, then.
Thanks. But hey, what are YOU\ndoing up at such an hour?
The embarrassing truth is that I was woken\nby a dream and can't get back to sleep.
I still have nightmares of the time\nI spent imprisoned by Thanatos.
I thought some dancing might help\ncalm me and take my mind off it.
But I still don't feel like I can sleep.
I'm not surprised to hear that.\nIt was a really terrible experience.
...Wait. I think I've got an idea.
Er, all right. But where are we going?
Here, I made you some hot milk.
So THIS was your idea!\nMmm, it smells lovely.
My mother always used to make it\nwhenever I couldn't sleep.
She sounds like a very kind person.\nThank you, {player_name}.
...It's a gentle taste.\nAnd the warmth puts me at ease.
Sleep should come easily after this.
Hey, somethin' smells great in here!\nIs it pie? Or maybe TWO pies?!
Ranzal? What are you doing here?
Thought I'd pop in here for a midnight\nsnack or three. Looks like my timin'\nwas spot on the nose!
Well, there's no pie, but we do have\nwarm milk. Would you like a cup?
I wouldn't miss a chance to sample\nsomething made by my darling.
All right, what's going on down here?
We can hear you all the way upstairs.
Huh?! Someone must have lost my invite\nto this party, but I'm crashin' it anyway!
Good grief. Did we wake EVERYONE?
All this just because I couldn't sleep.
You know what's best for times you\ncan't sleep? A FEAST!
A feast. ...In the middle of the night.
Sure! If you aren't sleepy, the best thing to\ndo is gorge yourself until you are.
Everyone has fun, THEN gets to ride the\nmidnight train to sacktown. We're killin'\na couple'a birds with one catapult!
I'm not certain that is the most\nappropriate way to describe this.
This sounds fun. Let's do it!
I suppose it DOES sound rather exciting\nnow that I think about it.
Well, if Felicia's in, we've gotta do it!
I think it's a good idea. Elisanne? Cleo?\nHow do you feel about it?
If you have no objections, neither do I.
Well then, what food does everyone want?\nIt wouldn't be much of a feast without any.
This is going to be great!
*BURRRRRRRRP* N-not another bite.\n...Maybe just one more ham?\nZzzzz...
All right, now it's my turn to be the\nentertainer...
Heh. Looks like they're all fast asleep.
Sorry, Felicia. This feast was really\nsupposed to be for you.
Yet here you are helping me\nput blankets over people.
Oh, please don't apologize. I feel like\nI'll be able to sleep soundly after this.
We've all been playing around like\nchildren, and I'm exhausted.
In that case, let's hit the hay.
I'm sure I'll have sweet dreams tonight.
If you ever can't sleep again,\njust tell us, all right?
